post_text: NOLA-PS is announcing school closures and cancelation of all school-based activities for Monday and Tuesday of this week due to Tropical Storm Marco. These closures will also affect the prepared meals being offered to families for pick-up.
shared_text:
Orleans Parish School Board
August 23 at 11:14 AM ·

NOLA-PS is announcing school closures and cancelation of all school-based activities for Monday and Tuesday of this week due to Tropical Storm Marco. These closures will also affect the prepared meals being offered to families for pick-up.

The District will continue to monitor the two storms over the next few days and will reassess needs for additional closures due to Tropical Storm Laura as we continue to learn more on the potential impacts to our area.

Read more at: https://bit.ly/2QgknJJ

#nolaed

post_text: Do you have a favorite teacher at Audubon? Nominate them to win a fun Back-to-School Basket from Reginelli's Pizzeria!
shared_text:
Reginelli's Pizzeria
August 3 at 10:10 AM ·

This school year is looking a little different than usual. 🍎 We are so thankful for teachers & educators everywhere for making sacrifices and adapting to the new normal. 👨‍🏫 In order to show our thanks, we are giving away a Back-to-School Basket filled with school supplies, cleaning supplies, a bottle of Reginelli's Reserve Wine & a $50 Reginelli's Pizzeria Gift Card. Nominate any teacher in the comments below and let us know what makes them an A+ teacher. Teachers--feel free to nominate yourself as well! You can nominate as many teachers as you'd like. 🍕 #PizzaWithPurpose
.
.
.
.
Entries will be accepted until 8/9/20. Winner will be contacted on 8/10/20. The winner will be be randomly selected. One winner will be chosen between all IG and FB entries. The winner must be 21 years or older to receive wine. The winner must be able to pick up the prize from New Orleans, Mandeville or Baton Rouge.

Audubon Schools
July 29 at 2:26 PM ·

In line with the updated guidance from NOLA Public Schools regarding safely reopening schools in August via a distance learning format for all students, Audubon has released our Distance Learning plan that details our commitments as a school in providing virtual learning, our expectations for our students, and examples of what a day in the life of our students may look like during distance learning.
text:
Visit auduboncharter.org for more information!
